title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Make a plan that return organisation names and the number of departments that they have. I want the output in descending order and outputted in a textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log: Create a plan that returns each organization’s name along with the count of departments it has. The results should be ordered in descending order by the number of departments. The final output must be written to a text file.

log.thoughts: Selected organisation and department tables to compute the number of departments per organisation.

steps.detailed_description: Load the organisation and department tables as inputs. Both tables will be used to compute the number of departments per organisation.
Join the organisation dataset with the department dataset on organisation_id. Input: organisation and department. Output: a combined dataset that links each organisation to its departments.
Group by organisation.name and count the number of associated departments, producing (name, department_count). Then sort the results by department_count in descending order.
Write the final ordered list (organisation name and department count) to a text file as the final output.

log.thoughts: A concise 4-step plan: load inputs, join on organisation_id, aggregate counts by organisation, and output the sorted results to a text file.
